      },
      "date": "2016-09-07 20:24:54.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-2\n\nJames, good idea.\n\nLi Xi, this kind of extra testing could be added into the commit message original patch if it needs to be refreshed for some reason.  I don't think that is needed right now, since the patch is ready to land, but is waiting for this patch to pass to avoid another case like LU-8565.\n\nMark as -2 since this patch is just for testing and not intended to land.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "9e2fe425f0bcf0c8f4b562bd87968ac5d4838db2",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2016-09-07 20:27:16.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nJames, one minor comment - when requesting a large number of tests to be run, it is better to split these into separate Test-Parameters: lines, so that they can be run in parallel.  As it is, with 8x sanity runs this will take about 19h to complete instead of maybe 10h to finish both runs in parallel.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
